<% seo_for title: "Privacy Policy",
           description: "How The Goal Atlas handles cookies, advertising, and analytics, including "  \
                        "Google AdSense advertising cookies and how to opt out." %>

<div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
  <%= render "shared/breadcrumbs", crumbs: [["Privacy Policy", nil]] %>

  <header class="mb-8">
    <h1 class="font-serif text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-[#f0c870]">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="text-[#8aa898] mt-3 leading-relaxed">Last updated: 18 June 2026</p>
  </header>

  <div class="space-y-4 text-[#e8d99c]/90 leading-relaxed">
    <p>
      This Privacy Policy explains what information The Goal Atlas
      (<a href="https://thegoalatlas.com" class="text-[#c89942] hover:text-[#f0c870] underline transition">thegoalatlas.com</a>,
      "we", "us") collects when you visit the site, how it is used, and the choices you have. By
      using the site you agree to the practices described here.
    </p>

    <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl text-[#f0c870] pt-6">Information we collect</h2>
    <p>
      The Goal Atlas does not require you to create an account, and we do not ask you for personal
      information to browse. We collect only:
    </p>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1">
      <li>
        <strong class="text-[#e8d99c]">Anonymous usage statistics</strong> — aggregate page-view
        data (such as which pages are popular and roughly where visitors come from), used to
        understand and improve the site.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong class="text-[#e8d99c]">Standard server logs</strong> — your browser and server
        may record technical details such as IP address, browser type, and the pages requested, as
        is normal for any website.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong class="text-[#e8d99c]">Advertising data</strong> — collected by our advertising
        partner as described below.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl text-[#f0c870] pt-6">Cookies and advertising</h2>
    <p>
      Third-party vendors, including Google, use cookies to serve ads based on a user's prior
      visits to this website or other websites.
    </p>
    <p>
      Google's use of advertising cookies enables it and its partners to serve ads to you based on
      your visit to this site and/or other sites on the Internet.
    </p>
    <p>
      You may opt out of personalised advertising by visiting
      <a href="https://www.google.com/settings/ads" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
         class="text-[#c89942] hover:text-[#f0c870] underline transition">Google Ads Settings</a>.
      Alternatively, you can opt out of a third-party vendor's use of cookies for personalised
      advertising by visiting
      <a href="https://www.aboutads.info/choices/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
         class="text-[#c89942] hover:text-[#f0c870] underline transition">www.aboutads.info</a>.
      For more on how Google uses information from sites that use its services, see
      <a href="https://policies.google.com/technologies/partner-sites" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
         class="text-[#c89942] hover:text-[#f0c870] underline transition">Google's Privacy &amp; Terms</a>.
    </p>
    <p>
      If you are located in the European Economic Area, the United Kingdom, or Switzerland, you
      will be asked for consent before personalised advertising cookies are set, and you can
      withdraw or change that consent at any time.
    </p>

    <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl text-[#f0c870] pt-6">Analytics</h2>
    <p>
      We use a privacy-focused analytics tool that measures traffic in aggregate. It does not use
      tracking cookies, does not collect personally identifiable information, and does not follow
      you across other websites.
    </p>

    <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl text-[#f0c870] pt-6">Essential cookies</h2>
    <p>
      A small number of strictly necessary cookies are used only for the password-protected
      administration area of the site. They are not used for ordinary visitors browsing public
      pages.
    </p>

    <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl text-[#f0c870] pt-6">External links</h2>
    <p>
      The Goal Atlas links to highlights and material hosted by third parties (for example official
      video platforms). Those sites have their own privacy policies, and we are not responsible for
      their content or practices.
    </p>

    <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl text-[#f0c870] pt-6">Your rights</h2>
    <p>
      Depending on where you live, you may have the right to access, correct, or delete personal
      data held about you, or to object to its processing. Because we do not maintain user accounts,
      we typically hold no information that identifies you personally. If you have a request or
      question, please contact us.
    </p>

    <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl text-[#f0c870] pt-6">Changes to this policy</h2>
    <p>
      We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Material changes will be reflected by the
      "last updated" date above.
    </p>

    <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl text-[#f0c870] pt-6">Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Questions about this policy can be sent to
      <a href="mailto:tuxnotfound@cioga.eu" class="text-[#c89942] hover:text-[#f0c870] underline transition">tuxnotfound@cioga.eu</a>,
      or see the
      <%= link_to "Contact", contact_path, class: "text-[#c89942] hover:text-[#f0c870] underline transition" %>
      page.
    </p>
  </div>
</div>
